{"lemma":"أَكِلَّة","slug":"أَكِلَّة","root":"ك.ل.ل","root_slug":"ك-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n992","n1002","n1003","n1004","n1005","n1006"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crown, garland, wreath, corona"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic כְלִילָא /ࡊࡋࡉࡋࡀ (klila) / ܟܠܺܝܠܳܐ (klīlā, “wreath, garland, circlet”), from Akkadian 𒄃 (GILIM /⁠kilīlu⁠/)."},"ipa":["/ʔik.liːl/","/ʔak.liːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n992","headword_ar":"اَكَلَهُ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolN","text_ar":"اَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okalN","text_ar":"مَاْكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K,) namely, food. (S.) Er-Rummánee says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolN","text_ar":"اَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swallowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"food"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after chewing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it; so that the swallowing of pebbles is not properly thus termed: (Msb:) or, accord. to Ibn-El-Kemál, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conveying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transmitting, to the belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"what may be chewed,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chewed or not;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that it does not apply to milk, nor to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiyq","text_ar":"سَوِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":": and as to the saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"mina AlA=kiliyna AlmaA='a ZulomFA famaA A^araY\n                      \n                     \n                        yanaAluwna xayorFA baEoda A^akolihimu AlmaA='a"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the eaters of"},{"kind":"text","text":"what they purchase with the price of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water, wrongfully, I do not see"},{"kind":"text","text":"any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attain good after their eating of"},{"kind":"text","text":"what they have purchased with the price of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] he means a people who used to sell water and purchase with the price thereof what they would eat: (TA:) [for you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akala ka*aA","text_ar":"اَكَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate the price of such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see another ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAfN","text_ar":"اـِكَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and another voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoYN","text_ar":"ثَدْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  The saying, in the Kur [v. 70],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^akaluwA mino fawoqihimo wamino taHoti","text_ar":"لَاَكَلُوا مِنْ فَوْقِهِمْ وَمِنْ تَحْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arojulihimo","text_ar":"اَرْجُلِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They should eat"},{"kind":"text","text":"things"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above them and"},{"kind":"text","text":"things"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath their feet"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means, their means of subsistence should be made ample; (Bd, TA;) by the pouring of the blessings of the heaven and the earth upon them; or by the abundance of the fruit of the trees, and the produce of the grains sown; or by their being blessed with gardens of ripe fruits, so that they should gather them from the upper part of each tree, and pick up what should have fallen upon the ground. (Bd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoqaTaEa A^akoluhu","text_ar":"اِنْقَطَعَ اَكْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eating became cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulN","text_ar":"اُكُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotawofaY A^akolahu","text_ar":"اِسْتَوْفَى اَكْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he completed his eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akala raw^oqahu","text_ar":"اَكَلَ رَوْقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate his life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became extremely aged, and his teeth fell out, one after another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yaA^okulu Aln~aAsa","text_ar":"هُوَ يَاْكُلُ النَّاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^okulu luHuwma Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"يَاْكُلُ لُحُومَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He eats men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eats the flesh of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he defames men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does so in their absence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the action thus signified may be ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with words, or by making signs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the side of the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hmz","text_ar":"همز"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in the Kur [xlix. 12],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayuHib~u A^aHadukumo A^ano","text_ar":"اَيُحِبُّ اَحَدُكُمْ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^okla laHoma A^axiyhi mayotFA","text_ar":"يَاْكلَ لَحْمَ اَخِيهِ مَيْتًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would any one of you like to eat the flesh of his brother when dead?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; defamation, or defamation of the absent, being meant thereby. (S, * Ibn-' Arafeh, Bd, Jel.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akala ganamiY wa $aribahaA","text_ar":"اَكَلَ غَنَمِى وَ شَرِبَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate"},{"kind":"text","text":"the flesh of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my sheep, and drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"the milk of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"means, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akala","text_ar":"اَكَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAliY","text_ar":"مَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ate, fed upon, devoured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consumed, my wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 2]. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalati Aln~aAru AlHaTaba","text_ar":"اَكَلَتِ النَّارُ الحَطَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire devoured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consumed, the firewood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalato A^aZofaArahu","text_ar":"اَكَلَتْ اَظْفَارَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHijaArapu","text_ar":"الحِجَارَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stones wore away his nails"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAwu fiY maroy^Y~K A^akalatohaA AlyaA='u","text_ar":"الوَاوُ فِى مَرْيىٍّ اَكَلَتْهَا اليَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroy^iY~","text_ar":"مَرْيِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has swallowed it up"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marow^uwYN","text_ar":"مَرْوُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": a phrase occurring in the 'Eyn. (TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akala Eumurahu","text_ar":"اَكَلَ عُمُرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He consumed his life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b11-  It is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umirotu biqaroyapK taA^okulu","text_ar":"اُمِرْتُ بِقَرْيَةٍ تَاْكُلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquraY","text_ar":"القُرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have been commanded to have given unto me a town which shall devour the"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA;) said to be Yethrib [afterwards called El-Medeeneh]; (TA;) i. e., the people of which shall conquer the [other] towns and make spoil of their possessions: or it denotes the superior excellence of that town; and is like the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA HadiyvN yaA^okulu AlA^aHaAdiyva","text_ar":"هٰذَا حَدِيثٌ يَاْكُلُ الاَحَادِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a tradition which does away with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overrules, the"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traditions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Sgh. K, TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolu Als~ik~iyni","text_ar":"اَكْلُ السِّكِّينِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~aHoma","text_ar":"اللَّحْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The knife's cutting the flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalaniy raA^osiY","text_ar":"اَكَلَنِي رَاْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikolapN","text_ar":"اـِكْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukaAlN","text_ar":"اُكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAlN","text_ar":"اَكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My head itched."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) An Arab was heard to say, [as is often said in the present day,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilodiY yaA^okuluniY","text_ar":"جِلْدِى يَاْكُلُنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My skin itches."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akila","text_ar":"اَكِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalN","text_ar":"اَكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a limb, or member, [and a sore,] and a piece of stick, or wood,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became corroded"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cankered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decayed, by the mutual eating away of its several parts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ay^tkl","text_ar":"ايتكل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[written with the disjunctive alif"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiytakala","text_ar":"اِيتَكَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^k~l","text_ar":"تاكّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akilati AlA^asonaAnu","text_ar":"اَكِلَتِ الاَسْنَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor. and inf. n. as in the next preceding sentence, (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The teeth rubbed together and wasted away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of age; (S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell out, one after another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke in pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became much broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^k~lt","text_ar":"تاكّلت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (S, Msb;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ay^tklt","text_ar":"ايتكلت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akilati Aln~aAqapu","text_ar":"اَكِلَتِ النَّاقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAlN","text_ar":"اَكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel experienced an itching and annoyance in her belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the growth of the hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the growth of the fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her fœtus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n1002","headword_ar":"اَكْلَةٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until one is satisfied."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEotaAdu A^akolataAni AlgadaA='u waAlEa$aA='u","text_ar":"المُعْتَادُ اَكْلَتَانِ الغَدَا=ءُ وَالعَشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That to which people are accustomed is two acts of eating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the eating of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the morning-meal and"},{"kind":"text","text":"that of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the evening-meal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukolapN","text_ar":"اُكْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulN","text_ar":"اُكُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1003","headword_ar":"اُكْلَةٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A morsel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small mouthful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of food. (S, Mgh, Msb, K.) [For the pl., see below.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalotu A^ukolapF waAHidapF","text_ar":"اَكَلْتُ اُكْلَةً وَاحِدَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ate one morsel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akla biA^axiyhi A^ukolapF","text_ar":"اَكلَ بِاَخِيهِ اُكْلَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate a morsel by means of"},{"kind":"text","text":"defaming"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said, in a trad., of a man who is on terms of brotherhood with another, and then goes to his enemy, and speaks of him in a manner not good, in order that he may give him a present for doing so. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small round cake of bread;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroSapN","text_ar":"قُرْصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroS","text_ar":"قُرْص"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukalN","text_ar":"اُكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as below. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulN","text_ar":"اُكُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomapN","text_ar":"طُعْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) which is also syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okalapN","text_ar":"مَاْكَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEm","text_ar":"طعم"},{"kind":"text","text":";) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An assigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed, means of subsistence; such as a grant of a tract of land; and a tax,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of a tax"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taxes; and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomapN","text_ar":"طُعْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA in explanation of the same and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okalapN","text_ar":"مَاْكَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEm","text_ar":"طعم"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and [it is also said that] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okalapN","text_ar":"مَاْكَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is assigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"granted, to a man, so that he is not to be reckoned with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called to account, for it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.:) [thus it applies to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any absolute grant, either of land, (as an allodium, an appanage, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or of revenue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukalN","text_ar":"اُكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and app. also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kaAlN","text_ar":"ا=كَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see below]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Al$~aYo'u A^uklapN laka","text_ar":"هٰذَا الشَّىْءُ اُكلَةٌ لَكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomap","text_ar":"طُعْمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akiylapN","text_ar":"اَكِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikolapN","text_ar":"اـِكْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Z, Sgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolapN","text_ar":"اَكْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Defamation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defamation of the absent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Z, Sgh, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw A^ukolapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو اُكْلَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikolapK","text_ar":"اـِكْلَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolapK","text_ar":"اَكْلَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who defames men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does so in their absence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","S","Z","Sgh","Kr","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1004","headword_ar":"اـِكْلَةٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one eats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: *) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilosapN","text_ar":"جِلْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikobapN","text_ar":"رِكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"posture of the eater, reclining or sitting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu AlA_ikolapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ الاـِكْلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he has a good mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukolapN","text_ar":"اُكْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last two sentences. ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an itching:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukaAlN","text_ar":"اُكَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, K,) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalaniY raA^osiY","text_ar":"اَكَلَنِى رَاْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which both are said to be inf. ns.,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akilapN","text_ar":"اَكِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so the last is written accord. to the correct copies of the K: accord. to Esh-Shiháb, in the Shifá el-Ghaleel, it would seem to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukolapN","text_ar":"اُكْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is at variance with the authority of the leading lexicologists: the same word,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akilapN","text_ar":"اَكِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also explained in the K as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease in a limb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"member, in consequence of which one part is [as it were] eaten by another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a meaning which I believe to be correct, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukaAlN","text_ar":"اُكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) although SM says,] but this is identical with the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an itching:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalaAnN","text_ar":"اَكَلَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a vulgar term for the same; and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kilapN","text_ar":"ا=كِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with medd, given as correct by Eth-Tha'álibee, in [his book entitled] the Mudáf and Mensoob, but disallowed by ElKhafájee. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY laA^ajidu fiY jasadiY","text_ar":"اـِنِّى لَاَجِدُ فِى جَسَدِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikolapF","text_ar":"اـِكْلَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I experience in my body an itching."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","TA","As"]},{"entry_id":"n1005","headword_ar":"اَكِلَةٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikolapN","text_ar":"اـِكْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1006","headword_ar":"اُكَلَةٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akuwlN","text_ar":"اَكُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}